claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus comprising:
a structure having an inner surface with a shape configured to substantially conform to an outer surface of a stringer, the structure having a first arm and a second arm, the first arm contacting a first surface of the stringer and the second arm contacting a second, different surface of the stringer;
a first number of pins extending from the first arm of the structure and a second number of pins extending from the second arm of the structure, wherein the first number of pins are configured to engage a first number holes in the first surface of the stringer and the second number of pins are configured to engage a second number of holes in the second surface of the stringer when the structure is placed over the outer surface of the stringer and to support the structure with respect to the stringer when a load is applied to the structure;
a number of members extending from the outer surface of the structure, wherein the number of members is configured to be connected to a part; and
a flange connected to the structure securing the structure in a locked position.

9. A clip for connecting to an aircraft stringer comprising:
a first arm having a first number of pins;
a second arm having a second number of pins;
a center portion, the first arm flexibly connected to the second arm at the center portion such that the clip has a flexed position and a locked position,
the first arm configured to contact a first wall surface of the stringer in the locked position and the second arm configured to contact a second wall surface of the stringer in the locked position, the first number of pins configured to engage a first number of holes in the first wall surface and the second number of pins configured to engage a second number of holes in the second wall surface; and a flange connected to the first arm and the second arm and securing the clip in the locked position.

13. A clip for use with a stringer, comprising:
a body having a first arm, a second arm, and a center portion, the first arm and the second arm flexibly connected at the center portion, the first arm configured to contact a first surface of a stringer, and the second arm configured to contact a second surface of the stringer, the body configured to transition between a flexed position and a locked position by flexing the center portion;
at least one pin affixed to the first arm, the at least one pin of the first arm configured to engage a hole positioned in the first surface of the stringer in the locked position and to disengage the hole in the flexed position; at least one pin affixed to the second arm, the at least one pin of the second arm configured to engage the hole positioned in the second surface of the stringer in the locked position and to disengage the hole in the flexed position; and a flange securing the first arm and the second arm in the locked position, the body configured to receive the load when the first arm and the second arm are in the locked position.
